    • Uses of Token in com.salesforce.omakase.parser

      Methods in com.salesforce.omakase.parser with parameters of type Token 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      String Source.chomp(Token token)
      Opposite of Source.until(Token), this will advance past the current character and all subsequent characters for as long as they match the given Token.
      String Source.chompEnclosedValue(Token openingToken, Token closingToken)
      Similar to Source.chomp(Token), except this expects the value to be enclosed with an opening and closing delimiter Token.
      Source Source.expect(Token token)
      Similar to Source.next(), except it will enforce that the current character matches the given Token before advancing, otherwise an error will be thrown.
      Source Source.expect(Token token, String errorMessage, Object... args)
      Similar to Source.next(), except it will enforce that the current character matches the given Token before advancing, otherwise an error will be thrown.
      Optional<Character> Source.optional(Token token)
      Similar to Source.next(), this will advance to the next character, but only if the current character matches the given Token.
      boolean Source.optionallyPresent(Token token)
      Same as Source.optional(Token), except it returns the result of Optional.isPresent().
      String Source.until(Token token)
      Advances the current character position until the current character matches the given Token.
